  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mission East - NGO call Afghanistan 2022-2023</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Save lives, promote wellbeing and human rights and build resilience for the most vulnerable populations affected by the Afghanistan humanitarian crisis, in Afghanistan and Tajikistan.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This grant is awarded to the Mission East project: Emergency humanitarian assistance, resilience building and support to local capacities and rights-based approaches in crisis affected communities and HHs in Takhar and Badakhshan provinces of Afghanistan, and refugees in Tajikistan.

The project has the stated overall objective: to save lives, build resilience and promote the rights and wellbeing of the most vulnerable groups affected by the current crisis, including refugees, internally displaced, returnees, host communities and other highly vulnerable groups and communities. Particular attention will be paid to the rights of women and girls, minorities, and the protection of groups and communities at risk of persecution</narrative>
  </description>
